concept_explanation.proxy_router:
**Spring Boot proxy router:**

```java
@Component
public class StranglerFigFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {
    private final FeatureFlagService flags;
    private final WebClient newOrderService;

    @Override
    protected void doFilterInternal(
            HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse res, FilterChain chain) 
            throws IOException, ServletException {

        if (req.getRequestURI().startsWith('/api/orders')) {
            String merchantId = req.getHeader('X-Merchant-Id');

            if (flags.isEnabled('new-order-service', merchantId)) {
                // Route to NEW microservice:
                forwardToNewService(req, res, newOrderService);
                return;
            }
        }
        // Default: route to legacy system:
        chain.doFilter(req, res);
    }
}

// FeatureFlag: control which merchants use new service:
public class FeatureFlagService {
    // Start with: beta testers only
    // Scale to: 10%, 50%, 100%
    public boolean isEnabled(String flag, String merchantId) {
        return switch(flag) {
            case 'new-order-service' -> betaMerchants.contains(merchantId) ||
                                       Math.abs(merchantId.hashCode()) % 100 < rolloutPercent;
            default -> false;
        };
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.dark_launch:
**Dark launch (parallel run):**
```java
// Run both old and new — compare output (user sees old result):
public OrderResponse darkLaunch(OrderRequest req) {
    // Execute on BOTH systems:
    OrderResponse legacyResult = legacyService.createOrder(req);
    try {
        OrderResponse newResult = newOrderService.createOrder(req); // shadow call
        // Compare results (log differences, don't expose to user):
        if (!legacyResult.orderId().equals(newResult.orderId())) {
            log.warn('[DARK LAUNCH MISMATCH] legacy={} new={}', legacyResult, newResult);
            metrics.increment('dark_launch.mismatch');
        }
    } catch (Exception e) {
        log.error('[DARK LAUNCH] New service error: {}', e.getMessage());
        metrics.increment('dark_launch.error');
    }
    return legacyResult; // User ALWAYS sees legacy result during dark launch
}
```

